ECLOGUE IX.—MOERIS.

ARGUMENT.-—Moeris recounts to Lycidas the missortunes of Menalcas, who had been ejected from his lands. Menalcas had distinguished himself in poetica] composition, and the dialogue turns upon poetry in general, each reciting passages, as his memory serves him.
